O:8:"stdClass":4:{s:3:"cid";s:17:"field:node:248735";s:7:"created";i:1516083761;s:6:"expire";i:0;s:4:"data";a:17:{s:4:"body";a:1:{s:3:"und";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:5:"value";s:1986:"<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>About Our Client</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Our Client is a global Industrial MNC with close to US$45 Billion worth of revenue and over 150,000 employees worldwide. They are now looking for a seasoned Learning &amp; Development Manager for the region to spearhead learning frameworks and strategies while working closely with the respective global subject matter experts (SMEs). &nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Job Description</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Reporting to the Director of Learning, you will conduct learning needs analysis, create learning roadmap and lead the development and execution of annual learning plans. In partnership with the technical SMEs, this role will drive the identification of foundational capabilities and drive the design, development, delivery and impact analysis of learning initiatives. You will also deliver commercial/ soft-skill trainings, orientation and onboarding while working closely with your local and remote team members in the region.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>The Successful Applicant</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">You must possess a Bachelor Degree with minimum 12 years of Learning &amp; Development experience at the regional level within a global multinational company. Experience working in an Industrial sector will be preferred. You also need to have excellent communication skill, positive attitude, maturity, resilience and ability to work in an ambiguous environment.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>What's on Offer</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The opportunity to spearhead Learning &amp; Development agenda for the growing region and autonomy to improve processes. You will bring in the best practices from relevant industries and apply them wherever possible with a view for a sustainable learning strategy.&nbsp;</p>
